-- Mauritius Vehicles Sales Rose 2.5% in 2011, l’Express Says
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-02-13T06:58:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/mauritius-vehicles-sales-rose-2-5-in-2011-l-express-says.html
Mauritius sales of imported vehicles
rose 2.5 percent to 12,000 units, l’Express reported, citing
Gilles Lalanne, chairman of the Motor Vehicles Dealers
Association.  New vehicles accounted for 65 percent of total sales, while
sales of vehicles of less than 1,250 cc almost doubled to 18
percent, he told the Port Louis-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  